title: Microwave-emitting pod that can sit on the bottom of heavy-lift drones (Walworth County Sheriffs Department)

communications.communication:
To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the Wisconsin Open Records Act, I hereby request the following records:

Any and all records regarding research, training, or any operations in Walworth County, Wisconsin, for the microwave-emitting pod that can sit on the bottom of heavy-lift drones. Any records, including sign out forms, for the use of microwave-emitting drones, radiation-emitting drones, radio frequency emitting drones, electromagnetic-emitting drones, RADAR-emitting drones, any drone operations, happening in Walworth County, Wisconsin.

If you would like to see photos of them on my property and videos of them stalking me, please let me know. I can also supply photos of the melted water bottles from the extreme high heat of some kind of heat weapon.

The requested documents will be made available to the general public, and this request is not being made for commercial purposes.

In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the request filled electronically, by e-mail attachment if available or CD-ROM if not.

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 10 business days.

Sincerely,

Debra Poulsen

title: Documents related to the drafting of a letter to the College Board rejecting AP African American Studies courses

communications.communication:
To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the Florida Sunshine Law, I hereby request the following records:

All memos, reports, transcripts and correspondence related to the drafting of a January 2023 letter to the College Board rejecting AP African American Studies courses.

The letter is described in this news 
https://www.tallahassee.com/story/news/education/2023/01/19/florida-ap-african-american-studies-class-rejected-education-officials-desantis/69823224007/

A copy can be found here
https://drive.google.com/file/d/1A7ooiX-5pyiCxxLbmrvyPKcD9rpo1u3H/view?usp=sharing

The response should include any unsent draft versions of the letter.

The response should include all related correspondence between members of the board, including:

Chair, Tom Grady
Vice Chair, Ben Gibson
Monesia Brown
Esther Byrd
Grazie P. Christie
Ryan Petty
Joe York

The requested documents will be made available to the general public, and this request is not being made for commercial purposes.

In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the request filled electronically, by e-mail attachment if available or CD-ROM if not.

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 10 business days.

Sincerely,

Ben Welsh

communications.subject: Freedom of Information Act Request: Ron DeSantis Military Record
communications.communication:
To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the Freedom of Information Act, I hereby request the following records:

The Official Military Personnel File (OMPF) including all Fitness Report and Counseling forms (NAVPERS Form 1610/2), the most recent Cumulative Record Of Training (NAVPERS Form 5300/16), the Background Summary (NAVPERS Form 1640/32), Officer Personnel Action Requests (NAVPERS Form 1301/85) and Form DD-214, for Ronald Dion DeSantis.

DeSantis is the governor of Florida and a former officer in the United States Navy.

Because DeSantis is seen as a likely candidate for president seeking election in the coming months there is an urgency to inform the public. Therefore, I request expedited processing of this request.

The requested documents will be made available to the general public, and this request is not being made for commercial purposes.

In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the request filled electronically, by e-mail attachment if available or CD-ROM if not.

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 20 business days, as the statute requires.

Sincerely,

Ben Welsh
